modules.description: Generates and manipulates OCaml AST nodes for internationalization, handling identifiers, function applications, and argument lists with location-aware constructs. Operates on Ppxlib and Astlib AST types, including longident, expressions, and location data. Rewrites module names and constructs localized function calls during ppx processing.

Provides functions for extracting and formatting localized strings, handling pluralization, and interpolating variables within messages. Works with string templates, message dictionaries, and locale identifiers. Used to generate dynamic user interface text in multilingual web applications.

Handles internationalization by generating and modifying OCaml AST nodes, supporting identifiers, function applications, and argument lists with location tracking. It works with longident, expressions, and location data from Ppxlib and Astlib, enabling module name rewriting and localized function call generation. Users can transform code during ppx processing to support multilingual outputs. For example, it can replace function calls with localized versions or adjust identifiers based on translation tables.
